      "updated_at": "2016-05-23 20:48:18 UTC",
      "body": "Doing that will probably hide bugs in the incremental version forever, like it did for scalac pre-2.12 optimizer. I recommend against it.\r\n\r\n*However*, it would definitely be good to be able to bypass the incremental version (but not as default), either with something like `scalafmt --all` or `scalafmtAll`."
    },
